[User toggles ON from dashboard]
[05:00] Zone 1 (AC unit) — MANUAL_ON — 2350.0W
```

---

### **Engineering Best Practices Embedded Here:**

| Feature | Why It's Critical |
|---------|-----------------|
| **Optocoupler isolation** | Prevents ESP32 from being fried by AC mains back-EMF spikes |
| **Active-LOW logic** | Safe default on firmware crash — loads stay powered |
| **10-second confirmation** | Blocks false trips from motor inrush currents (~1-2s) |
| **30-second cooldown** | Prevents relay mechanical chatter and wear |
| **Priority ordering** | Sheds least critical loads first (AC before heater before lighting) |
| **Zone 3 exclusion** | Never auto-trip essential circuits (phones, computers, medical devices) |
| **Manual override flag** | Dashboard commands take precedence over auto-logic |
| **Non-blocking loop** | PZEM reads never miss; Firebase timeouts don't block relay logic |
| **Event logging** | Every trip is logged to /events node for auditing |

